      • WSUriStreamParser.KeysAggregator

        public WSUriStreamParser.KeysAggregator(ParameterType parameter,
                                Business.Source source,
                                WSUriStreamParser.SourceKey<?,ParameterType> sourceKey)
        Creates a keys aggregator and adds immediately a source key to it.

        That constructor will invoke the #add(Business.Source, SourceKey) method.

        Parameters:
        parameter - the parameter that will be stored, so as to be able to generate the various business object URIs
        source - the source the source key is attached to
        sourceKey - the source key to register

    • Method Detail

      • getParameter

        public ParameterType getParameter()
        Returns:
        the parameter which has been provided at construction time, and which will be used so as to compute the URIs.

      • add

        public WSUriStreamParser.KeysAggregator<ParameterType> add(Business.Source source,
                                                  WSUriStreamParser.SourceKey<?,ParameterType> sourceKey)
        Registers a source key to the aggregator, for a given source.

        Note that invoking the method multiple times with the same source parameter value will just replace the existing source key.

        Parameters:
        source - the source the provided key belongs to
        sourceKey - a source key that will be registered for the given source
        Returns:
        the aggregator itself, so as to ease the usage
